<title>USA: Heilig-Meyers closes Rhodes merger.</title>
<headline>Heilig-Meyers closes Rhodes merger.</headline>
<dateline>RICHMOND, Va. 1997-01-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Heilig-Meyers Co said on Thursday that it closed its stock-swap merger with Rhodes Inc.</p>
<p>Rhodes shareholders of record on December 31, 1996, have the right to receive one share of Heilig-Meyers stock for every two shares of Rhodes stock, Heilig-Meyers said.</p>
<p>Heilig-Meyers said it expects to issue approximately 4.6 million common shares in a tax-free exchange and assume approximately $89.0 million of Rhodes debt.</p>
<p>Including 106 stores added from the Rhodes merger, Heilig-Meyers operates 934 stores in 32 states and Puerto Rico.</p>
